<div id="block-wh-petitions-wh-petitions-history" class="block block-wh-petitions odd">
    <h2 class="trigger"><a href="#" class="no-follow">History of Petitions</a></h2>

  <div class="toggle-container display-none">
    <p>The right to petition your government is guaranteed by the First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution.  Throughout our history, Americans have used petitions to organize around issues they care about from ending slavery, to guaranteeing women's right to vote, to the civil rights movement.</p>  </div>
